---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ViewportInfo from '../components/ViewportInfo.astro';
import Accordion from '../components/Accordion.astro';
import Dashboard from '../components/Dashboard.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-100">

    <ViewportInfo />

    <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-14">

      <div class="mb-10">
        <h1 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Astro Component System Demo</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">
          Three components, one dependency chain.
          Open the browser console to see <code>log()</code> output.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">

        <Accordion question="What does <code>defineComponent</code> do?">
          <p>
            <code>defineComponent(name, def)</code> registers a component definition with the
            system singleton. The system matches it against every
            <code>[data-component="name"]</code> element found during scan.
          </p>
          <p>
            If a component is rendered 50 times, <code>defineComponent</code> is called
            once — Astro deduplicates scripts automatically. The system creates 50
            independent instances, each with its own <code>AbortController</code>.
          </p>
        </Accordion>

        <Accordion question="How does the <code>AbortController</code> lifecycle work?">
          <p>
            Before calling <code>init()</code>, the system creates an
            <code>AbortController</code> for the instance and passes it as
            <code>ac</code> in context.
          </p>
          <p>
            Pass <code>&#123; signal: ac.signal &#125;</code> to DOM listeners and
            <code>system.on()</code> calls alike. On destroy, <code>ac.abort()</code>
            fires and removes all of them at once — no manual cleanup needed.
          </p>
        </Accordion>

        <Accordion question="How do <code>deps</code> affect initialization order?">
          <p>
            Components are sorted into <em>waves</em> using Kahn's topological BFS.
            All components in a wave initialize concurrently. The next wave only
            starts once every <code>init()</code> in the current wave has resolved —
            including async ones.
          </p>
          <p>
            The <code>dashboard</code> component on this page declares
            <code>deps: ['accordion', 'viewport-info']</code>, so it is guaranteed
            to run after both are fully initialized.
          </p>
        </Accordion>

      </div>

      <Dashboard />

    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }
</style>
